The Church of Rosslyn and the surrounding scenery on the seques- tered banks of the Esk, with the caves of Gorton and Hawthornden, are so universally known and admired as to render any description unnecessary. The ehurch itself is undergoing a somewhat unnecessary process of resto- ration, at the expense of the Earl of Rosslyn.
